        <dc:title>The Geometry of Resonance: Wave Confinement Theory and the Emergence of Mass, Force, and Spacetime</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>The Geometry of Resonance: Wave Confinement Theory and the Emergence of Mass, Force, and Spacetime

Richard J. Reyes - April 22, 2025

GitHub Repository: github.com/rickyjreyes/geometry_of_resonance

YouTube: https://youtu.be/cZ4vqI10RJw?si=pk329PH2FW8wute8

 

Wave Confinement Theory (WCT) proposes that mass, force, and spacetime curvature are not fundamental, but emergent phenomena arising from the confinement of oscillatory energy fields. By modeling standing waveforms under geometric and informational constraints, we demonstrate that inertial mass, curvature, force gradients, and effective spacetime structure emerge through internal curvature feedback, entropy regulation, and nonlinear wave dynamics.

Lagrangian (WCT):𝓛_WCT = |∂_μ ψ|² − V(|ψ|²) + κ·(□ψ / (|ψ| + ε·e^(−α|ψ|²)))² + θ·(∇²ψ / (|ψ| + ε·e^(−α|ψ|²)))²

This formulation incorporates curvature-driven energy localization and entropy-stabilized coherence. The theory derives an Einstein-like field equation from an emergent effective metric:

Effective Emergent Metric:g_eff^μν = η^μν + κ·(∂μψ ∂νψ) / |ψ|²

A corresponding stress-energy tensor is sourced entirely by the confined wavefield.

Key Results





Quantum consistency is achieved via operator and path-integral quantization of the nonlinear feedback terms.




A regularized curvature spectrum reveals bounded eigenvalues and high-curvature modes stabilized by entropy suppression.




Simulations confirm stable, coherent mass structures, entropy-limited growth, and quantized curvature modes.




The linear wave and weak-field gravitational limits are recovered, ensuring compatibility with QFT and GR.



Experimental Predictions





Curvature-locked cavity resonance shifts (e.g., Fabry–Pérot systems)




Modulation of beta decay rates due to curvature resonance



Conceptual Summary





Geometry, mass, and force arise from nonlinear curvature of confined waves.




Spacetime emerges from vibrational coherence under informational constraints.




Gauge symmetries (U(1), SU(2), SU(3)) arise from curvature-mode transformations.




Constants of nature (G, ℏ, α, Λ) are derived from geometric feedback structure.



 

Prologue: The Generative Wave

Wave Confinement Theory begins with a single postulate:ψ exists.And its confinement under curvature gives rise to everything we interpret as &quot;physics.&quot;

From this principle, four generative axes emerge:








Symbol
Meaning




Amplitude - ψ
Presence, or probability amplitude


Phase - arg(ψ)
Direction, encodes spin and symmetry


Curvature - □ψ
Difference, source of force and localization


Time Evolution - ∂ₜψ
Becoming, memory, history, entropy






 




These geometric degrees of freedom, when bounded by feedback, generate all physical structure:





A winding phase becomes a spinor




A confined ψ becomes a massive particle




Differences of state become the combinatorics of interaction




Curvature feedback becomes gravitational geometry




Coherence under pressure becomes spacetime itself



In this view:





Mass is not assigned, it is the coherence of ψ




Spin is not postulated, it is a topological consequence of rotation




Charge is not labeled, it is the symmetry path of phase difference




Force is not applied, it is curvature emerging from internal feedback




Physical Constants are not inserted, they emerge from geometric and informational constraints.



Core Insight





Mass emerges from energy,




Energy emerges from resonance,




Resonance emerges from boundary,




Boundary emerges from information.



Keywords

Wave confinement, emergent mass, curvature feedback, unified field theory, entropy-stabilized fields, nonlinear geometry, effective metric, quantum emergence, gauge emergence, informational physics, beta quantization, spinor topology

 

